                <!-- FAQ Section -->
                <div class="mb-14">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--ink)] mb-6 tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-3">
                        <details class="group bg-[var(--paper)] border border-[var(--line)] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--ink2)] group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">What is TMS therapy like?</span>
                                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--muted)] group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--line)] pt-4">TMS (transcranial magnetic stimulation) is a non-invasive procedure where a magnetic coil is placed against your scalp to stimulate specific areas of your brain. Sessions typically last 20-40 minutes, during which you sit in a chair while the device delivers magnetic pulses. Most patients describe a tapping or clicking sensation on their scalp. No anesthesia is needed, and you can drive home afterward.</div>
                        </details>
                        <details class="group bg-[var(--paper)] border border-[var(--line)] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--ink2)] group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">How long does it take to see results from TMS?</span>
                                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--muted)] group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--line)] pt-4">Most patients begin noticing improvement between weeks 2 and 4 of treatment. TMS works cumulatively — each session builds on the last. A full treatment course typically runs 4-6 weeks (20-30 sessions). Some patients continue improving for several weeks after treatment ends.</div>
                        </details>
                        <details class="group bg-[var(--paper)] border border-[var(--line)] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--ink2)] group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">Does TMS actually work for depression?</span>
                                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--muted)] group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--line)] pt-4">Yes. Multiple large clinical trials and real-world studies show TMS is effective for treatment-resistant depression. Approximately 50-60% of patients experience meaningful improvement, and 30-40% achieve full remission. TMS is FDA-cleared for major depressive disorder and has received FDA breakthrough device designation for OCD and smoking cessation.</div>
                        </details>
                        <details class="group bg-[var(--paper)] border border-[var(--line)] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--ink2)] group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">Are TMS patient stories medically accurate?</span>
                                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--muted)] group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--line)] pt-4">All patient stories on TMS List are reviewed by licensed medical professionals for accuracy. Individual testimonials represent personal experiences and outcomes vary. Stories marked as "composite" are based on aggregated real patient experiences and do not represent a single individual. We clearly distinguish between documented clinical outcomes and personal testimonials.</div>
                        </details>
                        <details class="group bg-[var(--paper)] border border-[var(--line)] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none">
                                <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--ink2)] group-hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">Can I share my own TMS experience?</span>
                                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--muted)] group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
                            </summary>
                            <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[var(--muted)] leading-relaxed border-t border-[var(--line)] pt-4">Yes. We welcome patient submissions. Share your story with us through our <a href="/contact/" class="text-[var(--accent)] hover:underline">contact form</a> and it may be featured (with your permission) to help others considering TMS. All submissions are reviewed by our editorial team.</div>
                        </details>
                    </div>
                </div>

